Lepidodendron.label: Lepidodendron
Lepidodendron.description: Lepidodendron — known as scale trees — is an extinct genus of primitive, vascular, arborescent plant related to the lycopsids. They were part of the coal forest flora. Wikipedia

Baragwanathia.label: Baragwanathia
Baragwanathia.description: Baragwanathia is a genus of extinct plants of the division Lycopodiophyta of Late Silurian to Early Devonian age, fossils of which have been found in Australia, Canada and China. Wikipedia

Diphasiastrum.label: Diphasiastrum
Diphasiastrum.description: Diphasiastrum is a genus of clubmosses in the plant family Lycopodiaceae. It is closely related to the genus Lycopodium, and some botanists treat it within a broad view of that genus as a section, Lycopodium sect. Complanata. Wikipedia

Huperzia porophila.label: Huperzia porophila
Huperzia porophila.description: Huperzia porophila, Rock firmoss, grows throughout the Appalachian province of the Eastern United States, but is rare east of the Appalachians, being most common in a north-south belt along the western plateau area. Wikipedia

Sigillaria.label: Sigillaria
Sigillaria.description: Sigillaria is a genus of extinct, spore-bearing, arborescent plants which flourished in the Late Carboniferous period but dwindled to extinction in the early Permian period. Wikipedia

Leclercqia.label: Leclercqia
Leclercqia.description: Leclercqia is a species of early ligulate lycophyte, known as fossils from the Middle Devonian of Australia, North America, Germany, and Belgium. Wikipedia

Pleuromeia.label: Pleuromeia
Pleuromeia.description: Pleuromeia is a genus of extinct spore-trees belonging to the order Pleuromeiales and class Isoetopsida. It was one of the most common plants during the recovery from the Permian-Triassic extinction event. Wikipedia

Isoetes histrix.label: Isoetes histrix
Isoetes histrix.description: Isoetes histrix is an aquatic pteridophyte native to the Mediterranean region, northwestern Africa, and the coasts of western Europe northwest to Cornwall. It occurs mainly in temporarily wet habitats, otherwise called vernal pools. Wikipedia

Haplostigma.label: Haplostigma
Haplostigma.description: Haplostigma is a genus of arborescent lycopod, found only in the early part of the Middle Devonian. Wikipedia

Huperzia nutans.label: Huperzia nutans
Huperzia nutans.description: Wawaeʻiole is a species of club moss in the Huperziaceae family. It is endemic to wet forests and cliffside shrublands on the islands of Oahu and Kauai in Hawaii. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Selaginella moellendorffii.label: Selaginella moellendorffii
Selaginella moellendorffii.description: Selaginella moellendorffii is a lycophyte that is an important model organism, especially in comparative genomics. Wikipedia

Lycopodiella cernua.label: Lycopodiella cernua
Lycopodiella cernua.description: Lycopodiella cernua is a plant in the family Lycopodiaceae commonly known as the staghorn clubmoss. The Hawaiian name for the plant is wāwaeʻiole, or "rat's foot". Wikipedia

Asteroxylon.label: Asteroxylon
Asteroxylon.description: Asteroxylon is an extinct genus of plants of the Division Lycopodiophyta known from anatomically preserved specimens in an Early Devonian deposit of chert at Rhynie, Aberdeenshire in North-East Scotland ... Wikipedia

Diphasiastrum complanatum.label: Diphasiastrum complanatum
Diphasiastrum complanatum.description: Diphasiastrum complanatum, common names Creeping Jenny or Northern Running-pine, is a species of clubmoss native to dry coniferous forests throughout the Holarctic Kingdom. Wikipedia

Huperzia selago.label: Huperzia selago
Huperzia selago.description:
Huperzia selago, Northern firmoss or Fir Clubmoss, is a plant in the genus Huperzia in family Huperziaceae.
In the past, this species has also been classified as Lycopodium selago. Wikipedia

Isoetopsida.label: Isoetopsida
Isoetopsida.description: The Isoetopsida is a class of the Lycopodiophyta. All living plants belong to the genus Selaginella in the Selaginellales or to Isoetes in the order Isoetales. Wikipedia

Lycopodiaceae.label: Lycopodiaceae
Lycopodiaceae.description: The Lycopodiaceae are a family of primitive vascular plants, including all of the core clubmosses. These plants bear spores on specialized structures at the apex of a shoot; they resemble a tiny battle club, from which the common name derives. Wikipedia

Lycopodiophyta.label: Lycopodiophyta
Lycopodiophyta.description: The Division Lycopodiophyta is a tracheophyte subdivision of the Kingdom Plantae. It is the oldest extant vascular plant division at around 410 million years old, and it includes some of the most "primitive" extant species. Wikipedia

Lycopodium annotinum.label: Lycopodium annotinum
Lycopodium annotinum.description: Lycopodium annotinum L. is a species of clubmoss native to forests of the Holarctic Kingdom. A new genus, Spinulum A. Haines, has been proposed for this and closely allied species, but phylogenetic ... Wikipedia

Lycopodium clavatum.label: Lycopodium clavatum
Lycopodium clavatum.description: Lycopodium clavatum is the most widespread species in the genus Lycopodium of the clubmoss family Lycopodiaceae. Wikipedia

Isoetes appalachiana.label: Isoetes appalachiana
Isoetes appalachiana.description: Isoetes appalachiana, commonly known as the Appalachian quillwort, is an aquatic pteridophyte that is widely distributed in the eastern United States. Wikipedia

Isoetes tegetiformans.label: Isoetes tegetiformans
Isoetes tegetiformans.description: Isoetes tegetiformans, commonly known as mat-forming quillwort or mat-forming Merlin's grass, is an aquatic pteridophyte endemic to the U.S. State of Georgia. Wikipedia

Selaginella.label: Selaginella
Selaginella.description: Selaginella is a genus of plants in the family Selaginellaceae, the spikemosses. Many scientists still place the Selaginellales in the class Lycopodiopsida. Wikipedia

Huperzia serrata.label: Huperzia serrata
Huperzia serrata.description:
Huperzia serrata is a plant known as a firmoss which contains the acetylcholinesterase inhibitor huperzine A. It is widely distributed over-the-counter as a nootropic and dietary supplement.
This species is native to India and southeast Asia. Wikipedia

Huperzia.label: Huperzia
Huperzia.description: Huperzia is a genus of Lycophyte plants, sometimes known as the firmosses or fir clubmosses. This genus was originally included in the related genus Lycopodium, from which it differs in having ... Wikipedia

Isoetes valida.label: Isoetes valida
Isoetes valida.description: Isoetes valida, commonly known as the strong quillwort or true quillwort, is an aquatic pteridophyte native to eastern North America. It is found primarily in the Appalachian Mountains from Pennsylvania south to Alabama and Georgia. Wikipedia

Selaginella rupestris.label: Selaginella rupestris
Selaginella rupestris.description: Selaginella rupestris is a species of spike-moss occurring in dry rocky places in eastern North America, including one locality in Greenland. It has a wide but sporadic range. Wikipedia

Huperzia lucidula.label: Huperzia lucidula
Huperzia lucidula.description:
Huperzia lucidula, shining firmoss or shining clubmoss, is a bright evergreen, rhizomatous clubmoss of the genus Huperzia.
They grow in loose tufts 14-20 cm long, occasionally up to 1 m long. Wikipedia

Huperzia megastachya.label: Huperzia megastachya
Huperzia megastachya.description: Huperzia megastachya is a species of firmoss found exclusively in Madagascar. Wikipedia

Isoetes louisianensis.label: Isoetes louisianensis
Isoetes louisianensis.description: The Louisiana quillwort is a small, grass-like aquatic plant of the family Isoetaceae. It is "one of the rarest quillworts in North America." Wikipedia

Drepanophycus.label: Drepanophycus
Drepanophycus.description: Drepanophycus is a genus of extinct plants of the Division Lycopodiophyta of Early to Late Devonian age, found in Eastern Canada and Northeast USA, China, Russia, Egypt and various parts of Northern Europe and Britain. Wikipedia

Selaginella elmeri.label: Selaginella elmeri
Selaginella elmeri.description: Selaginella elmeri is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Selaginella martensii.label: Selaginella martensii
Selaginella martensii.description: Selaginella martensii is a lycophyte in the Selaginellaceae family. It is native to Mexico and Central America. Wikipedia

Selaginella poulteri.label: Selaginella poulteri
Selaginella poulteri.description: Selaginella poulteri is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Selaginella pulcherrima.label: Selaginella pulcherrima
Selaginella pulcherrima.description: Selaginella pulcherrima is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Selaginella uncinata.label: Selaginella uncinata
Selaginella uncinata.description: Selaginella uncinata is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Isoëtes.label: Isoetes
Isoëtes.description: Isoëtes, commonly known as the quillworts, is a genus of plants in the class Isoëtopsida and order Isoëtales. They are lycopods. There are about 140–150 species, with a cosmopolitan distribution but often scarce to rare. Wikipedia

Selaginella apoda.label: Selaginella apoda
Selaginella apoda.description: Selaginella apoda, commonly known as meadow spike-moss, is a lycophyte native to much of the eastern United States and parts of northeastern Mexico. Wikipedia

Selaginella kraussiana.label: Selaginella kraussiana
Selaginella kraussiana.description: Selaginella kraussiana, sometimes known by the common names of Krauss's spikemoss and African clubmoss, is a clubmoss found naturally in the Canary Islands, the Azores and parts of mainland Africa . Wikipedia

Selaginella selaginoides.label: Selaginella selaginoides
Selaginella selaginoides.description: Selaginella selaginoides is a non-flowering plant of the spikemoss genus Selaginella with a wide distribution around the Northern Hemisphere. It resembles a moss in appearance but is a vascular plant belonging to the division Lycopodiophyta. Wikipedia

Lycopodiella.label: Lycopodiella
Lycopodiella.description: Lycopodiella is a genus in the clubmoss family Lycopodiaceae. The genus members are commonly called bog clubmosses, describing their wetland habitat. Wikipedia

Isoetes lacustris.label: Isoetes lacustris
Isoetes lacustris.description: Isoetes lacustris is a boreal quillwort native on both sides of the northern Atlantic Ocean. In Europe, it is distributed from Poland west to northeastern France, throughout Scandinavia, the west and ... Wikipedia

Selaginella carinata.label: Selaginella carinata
Selaginella carinata.description: Selaginella carinata is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Selaginella sericea.label: Selaginella sericea
Selaginella sericea.description: Selaginella sericea is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. It is endemic to Ecuador. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and subtropical or tropical moist montane forests. Wikipedia

Diphasiastrum digitatum.label: Diphasiastrum digitatum
Diphasiastrum digitatum.description: Diphasiastrum digitatum is known as Groundcedar or Crowsfoot, along with other members of its genus, but the common name Fan Clubmoss can be used to refer to it specifically. It is the most common species of Diphasiastrum in North America. Wikipedia

Isoetes nuttallii.label: Isoetes nuttallii
Isoetes nuttallii.description: Isoetes nuttallii is a species of quillwort, a type of lycopod. Its common name is Nuttall's quillwort. Wikipedia

Lycopodiella inundata.label: Lycopodiella inundata
Lycopodiella inundata.description: Lycopodiella inundata is a species of club moss known by the common names inundated club moss, marsh club moss and northern bog club moss. Wikipedia

Phylloglossum.label: Phylloglossum
Phylloglossum.description: Phylloglossum, a genus in the clubmoss family Huperziaceae, is a small plant superficially resembling a tiny grass plant, growing with a rosette of slender leaves 2-5 cm long from an underground bulb-like root. Wikipedia

Selaginella bryopteris.label: Selaginella bryopteris
Selaginella bryopteris.description: Selaginella bryopteris, known commonly as sanjeevini and sanjivini booti, is a lithophytic plant. It is used medicinally in India. The popular name sanjeevani which translates as "One that infuses life" derives from the medicinal properties. Wikipedia

Lycopodiopsida.label: Lycopodiopsida
Lycopodiopsida.description: The Lycopodiopsida are a class of plants often loosely grouped as the fern allies. Traditionally, the group included not only the clubmosses and firmosses, but also the spikemosses and the quillworts. Wikipedia

Isoetes eludens.label: Isoetes eludens
Isoetes eludens.description: Isoetes eludens is an aquatic plant in the genus commonly known as quillwort that is native to the Kamiesberg Mountains in Namaqualand, South Africa. Wikipedia

Lycopodium obscurum.label: Lycopodium obscurum
Lycopodium obscurum.description: Lycopodium obscurum, commonly called ground pine, prince's pine or princess pine, is a species of clubmoss in the family Lycopodiaceae. It is a close relative of other treelike Lycopodium such as L. dendroideum and L. hickeyi. Wikipedia

Selaginella oregana.label: Selaginella oregana
Selaginella oregana.description: Selaginella oregana is a species of spikemoss known by the common name Oregon spikemoss. It is native to the Pacific Coast of western North America, where it can be found from British Columbia to northern California. Wikipedia

Selaginella serpens.label: Selaginella serpens
Selaginella serpens.description: Selaginella serpens is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Selaginella umbrosa.label: Selaginella umbrosa
Selaginella umbrosa.description: Selaginella umbrosa is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Isoetes engelmannii.label: Isoetes engelmannii
Isoetes engelmannii.description: Isoetes engelmannii, commonly known as Engelmann's quillwort or Appalachian quillwort, is an aquatic pteridophyte and is the most widely distributed species of its genus in eastern North America. Wikipedia

Dendrolycopodium.label: Dendrolycopodium
Dendrolycopodium.description: The genus Dendrolycopodium is a clubmoss genus that some taxonomists have segregated from Lycopodium. It is treated as section Obscura when retained within Lycopodium. The genus includes a discrete group of plants with similar morphologies. Wikipedia

Isoetes bolanderi.label: Isoetes bolanderi
Isoetes bolanderi.description: Isoetes bolanderi is a species of quillwort, a type of lycopod. Its common name is Bolander's quillwort. This is a "primitive" aquatic plant native to western North America which grows almost entirely underwater in lakes and other water bodies. Wikipedia

Isoetes howellii.label: Isoetes howellii
Isoetes howellii.description: Isoetes howellii is a species of quillwort, a type of lycopod. Its common name is Howell's quillwort. This is a "primitive" aquatic plant native to western North America which grows in wet habitat such as vernal pools. Wikipedia

Lepidodendrales.label: Lepidodendrales
Lepidodendrales.description: Lepidodendrales were primitive, vascular, arborescent plants related to the lycopsids. They thrived during the Carboniferous period, and some reached heights of over 30 meters, with trunks often more than one meter in diameter. Wikipedia

Lycopodium dendroideum.label: Lycopodium dendroideum
Lycopodium dendroideum.description: Lycopodium dendroideum is a clubmoss native to the northeastern USA. It is part of a complex of species colloquially known as groundpine, which taxa were formerly lumped into the species Lycopodium obscurum. Wikipedia

Lycopodium deuterodensum.label: Lycopodium deuterodensum
Lycopodium deuterodensum.description: Lycopodium deuterodensum known as the bushy clubmoss is an ancient plant occurring in eastern Australia, New Caledonia and New Zealand. It is a spore-bearing vascular plant up to a metre high. Wikipedia

Selaginella asprella.label: Selaginella asprella
Selaginella asprella.description: Selaginella asprella is a species of spikemoss known by the common name bluish spikemoss. It is native to California and Baja California, where it has a disjunct distribution, occurring in the Klamath ... Wikipedia

Selaginella bifida.label: Selaginella bifida
Selaginella bifida.description: Selaginella bifida is a lycophyte native to Rodrigues Island in the Mascarene Islands. It was found firstly in 1991 on the Mont Limon at 20–150 m high and was confused with S. rodrigueziana Baker because of their strong phenotypical homologies. Wikipedia

Selaginella biformis.label: Selaginella biformis
Selaginella biformis.description: Selaginella biformis is a species of plant in the Selaginellaceae family. Wikipedia

Selaginella bigelovii.label: Selaginella bigelovii
Selaginella bigelovii.description: Selaginella bigelovii is a species of spikemoss known by the common names bushy spikemoss and Bigelow's spikemoss. Wikipedia

Selaginella cinerascens.label: Selaginella cinerascens
Selaginella cinerascens.description: Selaginella cinerascens is a species of spikemoss known by the common names ashy spikemoss, gray spikemoss, and mesa spikemoss. It is native to Baja California as well as some locations just north of the border in San Diego County, California. Wikipedia

Selaginella densa.label: Selaginella densa
Selaginella densa.description: Selaginella densa is a species of spikemoss known by the common names lesser spikemoss, prairie spikemoss, and Rocky Mountains spikemoss. Wikipedia

Selaginella eremophila.label: Selaginella eremophila
Selaginella eremophila.description: Selaginella eremophila is a species of spikemoss known by the common name desert spikemoss. It is native to the deserts and adjacent mountains around the intersection of California and Arizona with Baja California. Wikipedia

Selaginella hansenii.label: Selaginella hansenii
Selaginella hansenii.description: Selaginella hansenii is a species of spikemoss known by the common name Hansen's spikemoss. It is endemic to California where it can be found throughout the central part of the state, from the lowest ... Wikipedia

Selaginella wallacei.label: Selaginella wallacei
Selaginella wallacei.description: Selaginella wallacei is a species of spikemoss known by the common name Wallace's spikemoss. It is native to western North America from British Columbia to California to Montana, where it can be found ... Wikipedia

Selaginella watsonii.label: Selaginella watsonii
Selaginella watsonii.description: Selaginella watsonii is a species of spikemoss known by the common name Watson's spikemoss. It is native to the western United States, where it grows in many rocky habitat types, including high mountain peaks in alpine climates. Wikipedia

Selaginella lepidophylla.label: Selaginella lepidophylla
Selaginella lepidophylla.description: Selaginella lepidophylla is a species of desert plant in the spikemoss family. S. lepidophylla is noted for its ability to survive almost complete desiccation; during dry weather in its native habitat, ... Wikipedia

Isoetes melanospora.label: Isoetes melanospora
Isoetes melanospora.description: Isoetes melanospora, commonly known as black-spored quillwort or black-spored Merlin's grass, is a rare and endangered aquatic pteridophyte endemic to the U.S. States of Georgia and South Carolina. Wikipedia

Selaginella denticulata.label: Selaginella denticulata
Selaginella denticulata.description: Selaginella denticulata or Mediterannean Clubmoss is a non-flowering plant of the spikemoss genus Selaginella with a wide distribution around the Northern Hemisphere. Wikipedia
